 -- tTheory of Religion in a Pragmatic Philosophical Theology -- tAcknowledgments -- tContributors -- tIndex of Names -- tSubject Index 0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Varieties of Transcendence traces American pragmatist thought on religion and its relevance for theorizing religion today. The volume establishes pragmatist concepts of religious individualization as powerful alternatives to the more common secularization discourse. In stressing the importance of Josiah Royce's work, it emphasizes religious individualism's compatibility with community. At the same time, by covering all of the major classical pragmatist theories of religion, it shows their kinship and common focus on the interrelation between the challenges of contingency and the semiotic significance of transcendence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aPragmatism. 0aReligionxPhilosophy. 0aReligion--Philosophy. 4aCommunity. 4aContingency. 4aIndividualism. 4aPhilosophy of Religion. 4aPragmatism. 4aSecularization. 4amodernity. 4areligion. 4asemiotics. 4atranscendance. 7aRELIGION / Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aDeuser, Hermann, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJung, Matthias, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP / FUP eBook-Package 2016z978311071186840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823267590zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823267590423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823267590.jpg  a978-3-11-071186-8  NYUP / FUP eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL